<note id="fs-id1165042463715" class="checkpoint">
<exercise id="fs-id1165042463719">
<problem id="fs-id1165042463721">
<para id="fs-id1165042463723">Compare the growth rates of <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:msup><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1165042463747">
<para id="fs-id1165042463749">The function <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> grows faster than <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</solution>
<commentary id="fs-id1165042463772" type="hint">
<title>Hint</title>
<para id="fs-id1165042463780">Apply L’Hôpital’s rule to <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mtext>/</m:mtext><m:msup><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</commentary>
</exercise>
</note>
<para id="fs-id1165042463803">Using the same ideas as in <link target-id="fs-id1165043422462"/>a. it is not difficult to show that <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> grows more rapidly than <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mi>p</m:mi></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> for any <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>p</m:mi><m:mo>&gt;</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> In <link target-id="CNX_Calc_Figure_04_08_005"/> and <link target-id="fs-id1165043327297"/>, we compare <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> with <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> as <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">→</m:mo><m:mi>∞</m:mi><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
