<para id="fs-id1165042542902">Similarly, it is not difficult to show that <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mi>p</m:mi></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> grows more rapidly than <m:math><m:mrow><m:mtext>ln</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.1em"/><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> for any <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>p</m:mi><m:mo>&gt;</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> In <link target-id="CNX_Calc_Figure_04_08_006"/> and <link target-id="fs-id1165042460279"/>, we compare <m:math><m:mrow><m:mtext>ln</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.1em"/><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> with <m:math><m:mrow><m:mroot><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mroot></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:msqrt><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:msqrt><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
